{"id": "EUVD-2022-55169", "enisaUuid": "8c016c99-a7fb-31fc-b80d-5a470425f1bb", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nBluetooth: Fix a buffer overflow in mgmt_mesh_add()\n\nSmatch Warning:\nnet/bluetooth/mgmt_util.c:375 mgmt_mesh_add() error: __memcpy()\n'mesh_tx->param' too small (48 vs 50)\n\nAnalysis:\n\n'mesh_tx->param' is array of size 48. This is the destination.\nu8 param[sizeof(struct mgmt_cp_mesh_send) + 29]; // 19 + 29 = 48.\n\nBut in the caller 'mesh_send' we reject only when len > 50.\nlen > (MGMT_MESH_SEND_SIZE + 31) // 19 + 31 = 50.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:43:02", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:26:35", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ed818fd8c531abf561b379995ee7cc4c68029464", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2185e0fdbb2137f22a9dd9fcbf6481400d56299b"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49754"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "76aa34c7-cf83-3602-9c08-a33eb62ec220", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "8e2b7be1-712e-3cb3-bfd6-ec33c31429f6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "bbe91ca5-b995-30dd-8671-feb0f301dfa8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.1"}, {"id": "cb32ab1c-b8c8-31f1-bd93-470ac4ab8567", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b338d91703fae6f6afd67f3f75caa3b8f36ddef3 <ed818fd8c531abf561b379995ee7cc4c68029464"}, {"id": "d50319ec-8701-31ab-9293-c9106628fef0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b338d91703fae6f6afd67f3f75caa3b8f36ddef3 <2185e0fdbb2137f22a9dd9fcbf6481400d56299b"}, {"id": "e712538c-9324-3c88-bf55-a0867875d5d1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "bd0ca487-f9e2-3ae8-aa52-88399fa746c8", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}